1. CSS Stands for Cascading style Sheet.

2. CSS is used to control the style of a web document in a simple and easy way.

3. CSS is created and maintained through a group of people within the W3C called the CSS Working Group.

4. Three wasy of inserting a style sheet.
    *External
    *Internal
    *Inline

5. CSS ID and Class
    -The class selector is used to specity a style for a group of elements.
    -The id selector is used to specify a style for a single, unique element.

6. CSS Bacground Property
    CSS color specify =>
        - a valid color name - like "red".
        - a hex value like "#fff".
        - an RGB value like rgb(0,0,0);
        - an HSL (adanced);

    Background Image =>
        properties -> background-repeat (repeat-y, repeat-x, no-repeat).
                   -> background-size (cover, 100% 100%, contain).
                   -> background-attachment (scroll, fixed, local, initial, inherit).

7. CSS Fonts
    properties ->
        - font-family ("Arial, cursive";).
        - font-variant (small-caps).
        - font-size (16px, 2em).
        - font-weight (200, 300, bold , normal). *note - (min) 100 - 900 (max)
        -font-style (italic, oblique, normal).

8. Text Css 
    properties ->
        - color (same as default colors).
        - letter-spacing (b/w letters , 2px , 3px, 5px ).
        - word-spacing (b/w word , 2px , 3px, 5px ).
        - direction {
            ltr(left-to-right).
            rtl(right-to-left).
        }
        -text-indent (10px).
        -text-align (left, center, right, justify ).
        -text-transform (uppercase, lowercase, capitalize).

9. Link CSS
    properties ->
        - a:link (unvisited).
        - a:visited (visited). (clicked full).
        - a:hover (hover over it).
        - a:active (clicked down on it).

10. Border CSS
    properties ->
        - border-color (same as color).
        - border-style (dashed, solid, none, dotted, double, groove, ridge, inset, outset ).
        - border-width (2px, 3px ,5px ).
        - border-radius (10%, 50%, 2px, 15px).
            
11. List CSS
    properties ->
        - list-style-type (disc, circle, square, none, upper-roman[I, II, III, IV], lower-roman[i, ii, iii, iv], lower-alpha[a, b, c, d], upper-alpha[A, B, C, D] ).

12. Box Model CSS
    properties ->
        - Content (the element itself).
        - Padding (b/w content and border).
        - Border (b/w padding and margin).
        - Margin (after border).

12.5 NOTE: To use the shorthand property - the directions to use are as follows - Top -> Right -> Bottom -> Left.

13. CSS Scrollbars
    Overflow => types (overflow-x, overflow-y)
        properties ->
            -visible (shows the content as it is , no-scroll).
            -hidden (hides the extra content).
            -scroll (fits with scrollbar).
            -auto (automatically).

14. Position CSS
    relative =>
        properties -> 
            - assigns the position of child elements.
    absolute =>
        properties ->
            - gets positioned to any relative position.

14.4 NOTE: every div positions itself vertically taking all of the space ⬇️ .

15. Z-index
    properties->
        - the more z-index , the more image comes to top.

16. CSS Float
    properties ->
        - float-left(starts the element from left).
        - float-right (starts the element from right).

17. CSS Display
    properties -> (in CSS)(flex and grid are in CSS3)
        - Inline
        - Block
        - Inline block
        - None
        - grid(CSS3)
        - flex(CSS3)

18. Cursors
    properties ->
        - pointer
        - default
        - help
        - wait
        - move
        - crosshair
        - text
        - resize(n, e, s, w, ne,nw, se, sw, )
            north, east, south, west, northeast, northwest ... so on.